         <div type="translation" resp="#cmr" xml:lang="en">
            <p><note>i</note>:In this tomb lies the body of ? Fokion of good memory {he lived] by the mercy of Gof more or less 50 years. He left this world  on the twentieth day in December, 
               eighth indiction. May the Lord grant you rest eternal, and may light perpetual shine upon you. Dry bones, you will arise, and you will live  and you will see the majesty of the Lord..</p>
            <p><note>ii</note>: Sabaoth: Lord God: Christ.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>i. 2: D(e)i could perhaps be D(omin)i</p>
            <p>i. 4: ossa arida: see Ezechiel 37, available at <ref target="http://data.perseus.org/citations/urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0527.tlg053.perseus-lat1:37">Perseus</ref></p>
